      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "FIX IT FRED (1) was never in contention last time after settling well back at this track, but prior to that won by 2.25 lengths at this track (19.87) beating Ophidian in a Grade 5 on March 8. Form from his last run is proving strong. Should be very hard to beat this time. MAGICAL SAIDE (4) has a strong record this journey with three wins and a minor from six starts. Was out of placings last time (25.82) at Maitland in a Grade 5, finishing seventh and beaten 4.5 lengths. Looks suited here and can measure up. ROBELL POLLY (8) jumped from a low draw and boxed on well to finish second last time, beaten 2 lengths (20.20) behind Lollipop Valley at this track. Has performed well from this box with a win and two minor placings to her name from six starts. Expected to feature. COPY THAT (7) missed the frame latest (20.17) when fifth over 352m at Q Lakeside in a Grade 5. Has already won out of this draw.",
